Files:
- e2e/side-panel-group-transitions.e2e.ts (same file)

Context:
This is the reverse of US-001. Start with a matching tab open (plugin ready), close the tab, verify the plugin moves to the not-connected group.

```typescript
// Start with matching tab open
const tab = await context.newPage();
await tab.goto(testServerUrl);
await waitForLog(server, 'tab.stateChanged: e2e-test → ready', 15_000);

// Verify plugin is in ready section
await expect(sidePanel.locator('[data-radix-accordion-item]').filter({ hasText: 'E2E Test' })).not.toHaveClass(/opacity-70/);

// Close the tab
await tab.close();

// Wait for state change
await waitForLog(server, 'tab.stateChanged: e2e-test → closed', 15_000);

// Verify plugin moved to not-connected section
await expect(sidePanel.getByText('NOT CONNECTED')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });
await expect(sidePanel.locator('[data-radix-accordion-item]').filter({ hasText: 'E2E Test' })).toHaveClass(/opacity-70/, { timeout: 10_000 });
```

Constraints:
- Use the same test file and fixtures as US-001.
- Can be combined with US-001 into a single test (open tab → verify ready → close tab → verify not-connected).

Files:
- e2e/side-panel-group-transitions.e2e.ts (same file)

Context:
PluginList.tsx lines 138-142:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (animating.size === 0) return;
  setOpenReady(prev => collapseTransitioningItems(prev, animating));
  setOpenNotReady(prev => collapseTransitioningItems(prev, animating));
}, [animating]);
```

When a plugin transitions between groups, `collapseTransitioningItems` removes it from the open arrays, collapsing the accordion.

Test:
1. Open a matching tab → plugin becomes ready
2. Expand the plugin card (click to open accordion)
3. Verify `aria-expanded='true'`
4. Close the matching tab → plugin transitions to not-connected
5. Verify the card is now collapsed (`aria-expanded='false'`) in the not-connected section

```typescript
// Expand the plugin card
const trigger = sidePanel.locator('button[aria-expanded]').filter({ hasText: 'E2E Test' });
await trigger.click();
await expect(trigger).toHaveAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');

// Close matching tab
await tab.close();
await waitForLog(server, 'tab.stateChanged: e2e-test → closed', 15_000);

// Card should be collapsed after transition
await expect(trigger).toHaveAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false', { timeout: 10_000 });
```

Constraints:
- The transition animation is 200ms — wait for it to complete before asserting.
- Use { timeout: 10_000 } on the assertion to account for state propagation delay.
